Rsync file/directory to Remote Machine:
# rsync -a file1/Dir1 user@10.1.10.48:/tmp

Rsync Remote File/Directory to Remote Machine:
# rsync -a user@10.1.10.32:/home/cpleasant/Avengers.tar root@10.1.10.48:/tmp

Rsync directory/file to remote system with progress shown:
# rsync -avh --progress /home/rsync root@10.1.10.90:/tmp/

rsync -a /home/apps /backup/ -- Synchronize contents in /home/apps directory with /backup directory

Archive a file:
# tar -cf home.tar "home dir" -- Creates archive file called ‘home.tar’ from file ‘home’

Extract a tarball:
# tar -xf files.tar -- Extract archive file ‘files.tar’

View contents of a tarball:
# tar -tf files.tar

To archive and compress simultaneously:
# tar -zcvf home.tar.gz source  <-- Creates gzipped tar archive file from source folder

Compress a tarball:
# gzip file.tar -- Compression a file with .gz extension


cp source destination

cp file1 /tmp/
cp /home/username/file1 /tmp/

Copy Local File to Remote Machine:
# scp file1 user@10.1.10.48:/tmp

Copy remote file to remote machine:
# scp user@10.1.10.32:/home/cpleasant/Avengers.tar root@10.1.10.48:/tmp
